<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia to Have Good Harvest This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Russia is to get an
exceptionally big grain harvest this year - almost 80 million
tonnes, Russian President Boris Yeltsin announced today in his
radio address to the nation.
</P>
<P>
According to the Itar-Tass news agency, Yeltsin said that the
reason of the harvest is not only a good weather, but also the new
organization of farm labour.
</P>
<P>
The president meanwhile pointed out the problems in the
agro-industrial complex, saying "there is a shortage of investments,
efficient managers, and machinery, while the things we have are
supplied for 'extravagant' prices".
</P>
<P>
Russia should ensure its food independence and food
security, he said and emphasized that Russia must not only
provide itself with all the food but must also to export it.
</P>
<P>
In his address Yeltsin also noted the problem of privatization
of the state land, saying that "land in Russia must be sold and
bought. Just as customary in all the civilized world. It must be
the property of the farmer and he must decide himself what to do
with it." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
