<HEADLINE> China Hails New Party Leadership (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 19 (Xinhua) -- People throughout the country
celebrated today's successful conclusion of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the formation
of the new Party leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
They jointly pledged to study and carry out decisions made at
the congress, closely unite around the new Party leadership, and
hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory in order to
record new progress in all fields.
</P>
<P>
People in the Tibet Autonomous Region danced and rejoiced after
hearing of the Party's new central leadership.
</P>
<P>
Awangdanba, a local farmer who once posed for a photo with CPC
General-Secretary Jiang Zemin, said: "The good policies of the
Party have enabled Tibetan farmers to gain prosperity, and the
Tibetan people will forever whole-heartedly follow the leadership
of the Party."
</P>
<P>
Spontaneous applause erupted when local farmers in Xigang
Village, Helan County in the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region,
watched the live telecast announcing the new leadership.
</P>
<P>
"Farmers are 100 percent at ease under the guidance of the
Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core," said
71-year-old Hui Villager Zhao Guoming.
</P>
<P>
Xing Yichuan, an entrepreneur from southernmost Hainan
Province, noted that, "The key for holding high the great banner
of Deng Xiaoping Theory rests with selecting the the right
flag-bearer.
</P>
<P>
"The Party has selected a new collective central leadership
with Jiang Zemin at the core. This will serve as the fundamental
guarantee for the Party to realize its 21st century goals."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
