<DOCNO> XIE19970920.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Hails New Party Leadership (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Common Chinese citizens praised the fact that Deng Xiaoping
Theory has been adopted as the guiding ideology for the Party.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Hongqi, a retired factory worker from Chengdu, capital of
Sichuan Province, said: "Comrade Deng Xiaoping left his theory to
guide reform and our country will undoubtedly become more powerful
under its guidance and the leadership of the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core."
</P>
<P>
A Sichuan farmer named Huang Shulin said, "The Party Congress
has not only clarified orientation for China's future development,
but has more importantly written Deng Xiaoping Theory into the
Party Constitution. Farmers are now reassured."
</P>
<P>
The prefectural committee in Baise Prefecture in the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region where Deng Xiaoping had fought for the
CPC revolutionary cause assigned over 3,000 cadres to help local
farmers study Jiang Zemin's report to the Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Yuan, a former Red Army solder who escorted Deng Xiaoping
from Donglan to Hechi in 1931, said: "The third collective Party
leadership is energetic and high-spirited, and will lead the
country to victory on the road of socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
"The new leadership has confirmed Deng Xiaoping Theory as the
guiding ideology and we are 100 percent reassured."
</P>
<P>
Prof. Cai Qirui, an academician with the China Academy of
Sciences who lives in Xiamen, Fujian Province, said: "We should
think more about 'developing science for the motherland' as we
welcome the new century.
</P>
<P>
"I will exert all my efforts to fostering a new generation of
scientists for the country." 
</P>
</TEXT>
