<HEADLINE> France Again Appeals for Ceasefire by Congolese Parties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 19 (Xinhua) -- France today again appealed to
the warring factions of the Congo Republic to reach a ceasefire
and renewed its support to the mediation to the conflict offered
by Gabonese President Omar Bongo.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine met with the United
Nations envoy for Congo Mohamed Sahnoun, who was in Paris to
inform the French government about the mediation in the Congo
conflict, said French Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques
Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
Rummelhardt said that the on-going fighting between the forces
loyal to President Pascal Lissouba and the militiamen of former
president General Denis Sassou Nguesso is "very worrying".
</P>
<P>
"If the parties really have the political will to reach a
negotiated settlement, it is indispensable, as has stressed
Congolese Prime Minister Bernard Kolelas, that a ceasefire
intervene with the shortest delay," said the spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
