<HEADLINE> Tonkov Takes 13th Stage of Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Pavel Tonkov of Russia took
Friday's 13th stage of the Tour of Spain cycling, a 196-km ride
between Ponferrada and Valgrande Pajares in the north of Spain.
</P>
<P>
Alex Zulle of Switzerland retained his overall lead to keep the
yellow jersey, followed by of his compatriot Laurent Dufaux and
Spaniard Fernando Escartin in the second and third places
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Tonkov surged away from the leading group several kilometers
from the finishing line of the steep climb to Valgrande Pajares,
which is 1,450 meters above sea level.
</P>
<P>
Tonkov arrived at the finish half a minute ahead of Spanish
Jose Maria Jimenez. The three overall leaders were less than a
minute back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
