<HEADLINE> Kim Jong Il Congratulates Jiang Zemin's Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Kim Jong Il, leader of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), today congratulated
Jiang Zemin on his re-election to the leadership of the Communist
Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Kim, chairman of the National Defense Commission of DPRK and
Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army, sent a message to
Jiang, general secretary of the CPC's Central Committee and
chairman of its Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's re-election earlier in the day by the 15th CPC National
Congress, the DPRK leader said, reflected "the respect and trust
he has enjoyed from CPC party members and the Chinese people."
</P>
<P>
Kim wished the Chinese people, under the leadership of the CPC
headed by Jiang, to make great achievements in fulfilling the
missions put forward at the party congress.
</P>
<P>
Kim also believed that the traditional friendship between the
DPRK and China will be further strengthened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
