<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Joins KEDO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 19 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)
announced today that it formally joined the Korean Peninsula
Energy Development Organization (KEDO).
</P>
<P>
EU said that this would pave the way for a more important
European political and economic role in East Asia.
</P>
<P>
EU will join the efforts of the original KEDO members, South Korea,
Japan and the United States to implement KEDO's objectives.
</P>
<P>
KEDO, set up in March 1995 amid growing fears over safety and
nuclear proliferation connected with the nuclear energy program of
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), is responsible
for providing DPRK with light water reactors in exchange for
DPRK's agreement to freeze its nuclear program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
