week's workshop dubbed "Towards a Stable Policy", jointly
organized by the State House Correspondents' Association and the
office of the chief press secretary to the head of state.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Nigeria's Special Duties Minister
Alhaji Wada Nas said in a statement in Lagos Thursday that there
is no truth in the reports that Abacha is ill.
</P>
<P>
He accused the magazines of failing to provide any evidences
in their reports and called them "agents of destabilization" who
have their "base motives".  
