<HEADLINE> Half of Hungry People Worldwide to Get Enough </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Director General of the
Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO)
Jacques Diouf said today that half of the 800 million people
exposed to food deficit in the world will get enough food in 2015.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by the FAO chief in a statement he
issued on arrival here for a two-day visit to Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Diouf said, according to the decisions made by the world food
summit, half of the 800 million people exposed to food deficit
will be in a position to get enough food in 2015.
</P>
<P>
On his current visit to Ethiopia, Diouf said he will hold
talks with Ethiopian government officials on the
implementation in the country of the plan of action drafted on
the basis of the decisions the world food summit had passed to
guarantee food security.
</P>
<P>
He said, the program devised to attain food security, which is
now being carried out in Ethiopia in collaboration with FAO, is
one of the issues to be discussed.
</P>
<P>
The program is aimed at boosting agricultural productivity,
doing away with traditional farming, he added.
</P>
<P>
Diouf, former president of Senegal, was elected as FAO
director general in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
