<HEADLINE> India Cancels Debts to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister
Kumar Gujral today pledged to cancel his country's debt to
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Indian prime minister told a press conference in
the State House here that the money should be invested in
development activities, though he did not mention the amount of
the debt.
</P>
<P>
