saying that his country is proud to have played a modest part in
Tanzania's economic development programs.
</P>
<P>
Gujral said that India and Tanzania have been partners in the
common endeavor to establish a more equitable economic order and
to overcome the challenges of development in the world.
</P>
<P>
On the reforms at the United Nations, the Indian premier
called for continued consultations, saying, "The process of U.N.
reforms has reached a decisive phase. The aim of these reforms
should, therefore, be to strengthen the world body and to enhance
its development role so that it serves the interests of the
overwhelming majority of its members."
</P>
<P>
Gujral arrived here on Thursday to pay a three-day visit to
Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
