cope with the prevailing food shortage because of drought.
</P>
<P>
Norway and Britain also said they are ready to send food
relief to Ethiopia which was hit by rain failure in crop growing
regions during the little rain season of February to May this
year.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued today by the Commission of
Disaster Prevention and Preparedness of the Ethiopian government,
WFP has pledged to raise 30,000 tons of food out of which 8,000
tons has already been committed by Australia.
</P>
<P>
The government of Norway is taking measures to bring into
Ethiopia 6,000 tons of food aid through Norwegian donor
agencies operating in Ethiopia, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The British government has also expressed readiness to
dispatch 1,000 tons of food aid through Save the Children
UK, it added. 
