States.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Friday prayer goers at Tehran University, Major
General Seyyed Yahya Safavai, commander of Iran's elite Islamic
Revolution Corps (IRGC), warned that Iran faces major threat from
the presence of the U.S. forces in the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
He said the U.S. is working to destabilize the region "by
supporting Turkey's secular government and the Zionist entity
(Israel)" to weaken Iran's role of maintaining regional peace and
security.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has reportedly deployed the Fifth Fleet of the navy
and a total of 20,000 troops in the Gulf region, which has 60
percent of the world oil reserves.
</P>
<P>
Safavai said the U.S. views Iran as its major regional enemy,
so "it tries to have an active presence in the region to stand
against Iran."
</P>
<P>
But he stressed that "IRGC forces and volunteers would
immediately, effectively and decisively respond to any form of
aggression and attack from alien enemies."
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, he called on the Iranian forces to further
strengthen itself, saying that he saw "the need for further
beefing up the armed forces." 
