<HEADLINE> Historic Importance of Party Congress (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Since 1992, over 70,000 copies of "Farmers Reader on Deng
Xiaoping Theory" have been sold in Mengzhou City, central China's
Henan Province. Farmers have flocked to local bookstores over the
past two days asking when documents of the 15th Party Congress
will be published.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xiyu, a local villager, said: "General Secretary Jiang's
speech on Deng Xiaoping Theory fully represents the views of
farmers." He emphasized that he will read more of Deng's works and
will follow his road to develop the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Taiping Village, Linli County, Hunan Province, which Jiang
visited on March 25, 1995, is now well-off, with the village
having over 20 enterprises with assets valued at over 600 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Wu Zhiquan, general manager of the village enterprise group,
said: "Accomplishments in our village would have been impossible
without the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory and the reform and
opening policies."
</P>
<P>
"Taiping's prosperity would not exist had it not been for the
Party's policy of encouraging people to become wealthy," said Wu.
</P>
<P>
Local officials in Bose, in south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, are visiting grass roots units to publicize the
successes of the Party Congress. At the same time, Guizhou
University is offering special courses to study documents of the
congress and Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
Ye Weizhen, a member of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference National Committee who lives in Beijing,
told Xinhua that it is essential to have a complete understanding
of Deng Xiaoping Theory in order to completely and precisely carry
out the policies of the 15th Party Congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
