<HEADLINE> Historic Importance of Party Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 20 (Xinhua) -- People throughout China have
engaged in intense discussion related to the epoch-making 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) which
ended on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
People throughout the nation share the common view that the
congress presented a blueprint which can be realized through the
joint efforts of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
The key to implementing the decisions of the congress centers
on firmly holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory in
order to strengthen ideology and march forward by uniting around
the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Managers of large and medium-sized enterprises in Shenyang,
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, held discussions
concerning the decision of the congress to further restructure the
state sector.
</P>
<P>
The managers shared the common view that adopting Deng Xiaoping
Theory as the Party's guiding ideology fits the requirements of
the times and fulfills the will of the people. They noted that
this particular contribution marks the historic significance of
the congress.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 members from the "Students Research Society on Deng
Xiaoping Theory" at Shanghai's Jiaotong University exhibited great
interest in the congress. Deputy-Director Dong Xiaofeng told
Xinhua that the whole world has expressed great concern concerning
China's direction following the death of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese people are reassured by the fact that the Party
has established Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guiding principle by
writing it into the Party Constitution," said Dong. "Young
students are more confident about the future of the Party, the
country and the nation."
</P>
</TEXT>
