<HEADLINE> Largest Hydropower Station in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Four generating units at the
Yamzho Yumco Hydropower Station, the largest and most advanced
station of its kind in the southwest China's Tibet Autonomous
Region, recently went into operation and is working smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The success can be attributed to the great efforts of local
people and the support of the central government and people
throughout the nation, according to Gyam Co, vice-chairman of the
regional government.
</P>
<P>
The power station, a state key project, will greatly ease the
power shortage in Lhasa and nearby areas, and will promote the
speedy construction of power grids in the region's central
areas. The station is expected to boost economic development in
Tibet and greatly improve the living standards of local people.
</P>
<P>
The station, which sits at the highest elevation above sea
level of any similar plant in the country, was completed over an
eight year period with the support of many sectors, including the
State Planning Commission, The Ministry of Power Industry and the
State Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee and State Council will, as always,
adopt effective measures to support the construction of the power
industry in Tibet in order to meet the demand for power in the
region, according to a congratulatory State Council message
concerning the station's operations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
