<HEADLINE> Cholera, Famine Claim 138 in Indonesian Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 138 people have died
in an outbreak of cholera and famine in Jayawijaya District of
Indonesia's Irian Jaya Province since mid-August, the Antara News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Provincial Governor Jacob Pattipi vowed today to take immediate
action on the food shortage in Jayawijaya District. The local
government has already sent tons of rice to the district, the
governor was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the report quoted District Head Jb. Wenas as saying,
"The number of victims is expected to rise because many remote
villages in the district have not yet been monitored due to the
lack of transportation."
</P>
<P>
Wenas said teams of doctors have already been sent to the area
to distribute medicine and identify the cause of the outbreak.
</P>
<P>
Irian Jaya is on the Indonesian side of the huge New Guinea
Island which has been hit by severe drought as a result of the El
Nino weather phenomenon in the Pacific Ocean.
</P>
<P>
Other parts of Indonesia have also been hit by the drought
which has begun affecting the country's rice, coffee, cocoa and
corn production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
