<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti, US Troops Hold Joint Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and the United
States started a joint military exercises in Kuwait from today,
which will involve 1,500 U.S. troops as well as Kuwaiti land and
air forces, Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Without giving a time frame of the maneuvers, the agency said
it was in line with the "Intrinsic Action 3/97" war games which
took place earlier this year. The Intrinsic Action series of
war games, which were aimed at joint training of the Kuwaiti armed
forces, started in October last year.
</P>
<P>
The agency said this joint exercises was aimed at improving
the offensive capabilities of the Kuwaiti combatants.
</P>
<P>
It said that British and Italian troops would also join in the
later stage of the exercises.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and its western allies held dozens of various kinds
of military exercises since the Gulf War in 1991 within the
framework of military cooperation agreements.
</P>
<P>
The latest multi-national joint exercises was held in Kuwait
in April with the U.S., British and French warships. Military
sources said it was aimed at coordinating the ability of
coalition naval forces in providing mutual support as a team
against multi-threat. 
</P>
