<HEADLINE> Tianjin Port Accelerates Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The construction of coke and
nonferrous ore berths in the Nanjiang Section of Tianjin Port has
just begun, which marks the port's accelerated construction effort.
</P>
<P>
The two deep-water berths, with the capacity to service 100,000
dwt and 35,000 dwt vessels, will have a total annual handling
capacity of 10 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Nanjiang Section, which will eventually
cover 20 square kilometers, commenced in 1990. The section will
basically handle petroleum, coal and chemicals.
</P>
<P>
The three berths in operation have an annual handling capacity
of 10 million tons, and in 1996 alone handled over 1.24 million
tons of petroleum products.
</P>
<P>
Some 13 Chinese and foreign companies have invested 2.16
billion yuan to construct a number of industrial and office
buildings, as well as oil storage tanks.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the Nanjiang Section to eventually build a
150,000-ton oil berth and a coal wharf with annual handling
capacity of 20 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
