see any sign of a rise of that.
</P>
<P>
The ministers and governors discussed the recent currency
crisis in Southeast Asia, the economy of Asia and matters related
to the annual meetings of the World Bank and International
Monetary Fund to be held on September 23-25 in Hong Kong, Rubin
said.
</P>
<P>
Other matters discussed at the meeting include the poverty in
Africa and the situation in Russia, he added.
</P>
<P>
The G-7 groups Britain, Canada, France, Germany, Italy, Japan
and the United States. Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Anatoly
Chubais joined the meeting later.  
