<HEADLINE> Iran Stages War Games Against Chemical </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Some 200,000 Iranian army
soldiers staged a counter-offensive war game against chemical
attacks on Friday, the fourth day of military maneuvers, near
Qom, 150 kilometers south of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Today's Persian daily Jomhuri Islami reported that the armored
and mechanized rangers of the army repelled the chemical attacks
by the hypothetical enemy and cleared the area of chemical
contamination during the war games.
</P>
<P>
Iranian forces and civilians came under Iraqi chemical attacks
during the 1980-88 war between the two countries. Since last year,
defense against chemical attacks has become an integral part of
most military and civil defense maneuvers in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier Mohammad Mehrvarz was quoted by the daily as saying
the the maneuvers were the practical exercise of a legitimate
defense. "We have utilized the worthwhile experience of the era of
the Sacred Defense (war with Iraq) in these maneuvers," he added.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the maneuvers started on Tuesday in a
900-square-kilometer area south of Qom Salt Lake and will
continue till the end of the Defense week which will begin on
September 22.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Tehran Radio reported here today that the second
phase of the maneuvers continued this morning in Koushk-e Nosrat,
near Qom.
</P>
<P>
In the maneuvers today, the Airborne Division of the Army
provided defensive coverage for tanks such as T-72, Chieftain
and Dhol-Faqar, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The paratroopers belonging to Brigade-55 of the Airborne
Division of the Army also took part in today's operation which
cut off the connection between the enemy and its surrounding
forces.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Major General Seyyed Yahya Safavai, Commander of
Iran's Islamic Revolution Corps (IRGC), said that Iran will
further beef up its armed forces in order to deal with aggressions
of foreign powers, especially the United States.
</P>
<P>
He warned that Iran faces major threat from the military
presence of the American forces in the Persian Gulf, adding "the
aliens are working on creating a destabilizing effect by
supporting Turkey' laical government and the Zionist entity as
the new powerful force in the region."
</P>
<P>
This is designed to "defuse Iran's powerful and decisive role
in bringing peace and security in the Persian Gulf region, Central
Asian Republics and the Caucasus," he said.
</P>
<P>
The commander said that Iran is fully prepared to stand
against any attack or transgression, adding "IRGC forces and
volunteers will immediately, effectively and decisively respond
to any form of aggression and attack from alien enemies." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
