<HEADLINE> 70 Years' Devotion to Education Marked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 20 (Xinhua) -- A celebration marking the 70
year career of Su Buqing, a renowned Chinese mathematician and
educationist, was held today in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Su, 95, has worked a teacher since 1927 and has long enjoyed an
excellent reputation amongst mathematicians both at home and
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Today's celebration featured congratulatory messages from many
government departments and organizations, including the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), the State Education Commission, the Chinese
Academy of Sciences, and Fudan and Zhejiang universities.
</P>
<P>
Su has been an advocate of combining teaching with
research. "achieving effective teaching requires a reliance on
scientific research and and increased understanding of trends in
the development of new subjects," said Su..
</P>
<P>
Su, regarded as "the leading geometrician in the East" by
experts from Germany, Britain and the United States, has published
150 papers for both domestic and overseas academic publications an
has authored a dozen specialized books.
</P>
<P>
"Professor Su, who has continuously worked in the forefront of
the education cause, has set a good example for all the teachers,"
according to Yang Fujia, president of Fudan University.
</P>
<P>
Su, vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, attributed
his achievements to the Communist Party of China and the Chinese
people. "I will always remember the kindness of the Party and the
people," said Su. 
</P>
</TEXT>
