<HEADLINE> 14 Killed in Helicopter Crash in Southern Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people were killed
in a helicopter crash in southern Thailand late Friday night,
local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the dead, including many high-ranking military
officers, were airlifted to Bangkok earlier today and Thai Prime
Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh and other top Thai military
officers went to the airport to assess the situation.
</P>
<P>
The Thai military helicopter reportedly was carrying 21 people
who escorted Thai Queen Sirikit Kittiyakara to inspect southern
Thailand when it crashed.
</P>
<P>
The queen was not on the helicopter when the accident took
place, reportedly due to the bad weather.
</P>
<P>
The other seven people aboard the helicopter were also injured
and five of them were airlifted back to a hospital in Bangkok
today.  
