<HEADLINE> Premier Li Peng Arrives in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng arrived
here from Beijing by air this afternoon to attend the World
Bank/International Monetary Fund (IMF) Annual Meetings scheduled
for September 23-25 in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
As head of government of the host country, Li is to deliver a
speech at the opening ceremony of the meetings on September 23.
</P>
<P>
At 4:15 p.m. today, Li's special plane landed at Hong Kong's
Kai Tak International Airport, where he was greeted by more than
one hundred local officials and youngsters.
</P>
<P>
This is Li Peng's second trip to Hong Kong in less than three
months. On June 30, he and President Jiang Zemin came to Hong Kong
for the grand ceremonies marking Hong Kong's handover to China.
</P>
<P>
The premier is accompanied on the trip by his wife Zhu Lin,
Deputy Secretary-General of the State Council He Chunlin, and
others.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) Tung Chee Hwa and his wife Betty Tung, Head and Deputy Head
of the Chinese government delegation to the WB/IMF meetings Liu
Zhongli and Dai Xianglong, as well as principal officials of the
SAR greeted Li Peng and his party at the airport.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for the WB/IMF annual meetings to be
held in China. Financial ministers and central bank governors from
181 member countries of the two organizations, as well as
government leaders of some foreign countries, will attend the
meetings.
</P>
<P>
In addition, over 4,000 people from financial and economic
circles worldwide and more than 2,000 journalists will also be
participating, making this year's event the largest ever in WB/IMF
history. 
</P>
