<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Executive Board Agrees on SDR Allocation Proposal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Board of the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) has reached agreement on a
proposal to enable all members to receive an equitable share of
cumulative Special Drawing Right (SDR) allocations, a statement
from the IMF said today.
</P>
<P>
Under the proposal, a special one-time allocation of SDRs will
be made to equalize members' ratios of cumulative allocations to
their previous quotas at approximately 29.32 percent, according to
the statement.
</P>
<P>
The new allocation, involving 21.4 billion SDRs, will result in
a doubling of SDRs already allocated to 42.9 billion SDRs.
</P>
<P>
The proposal will be submitted for approval by the IMF Board of
Governors at the forthcoming annual meeting starting in Hong Kong
next Tuesday, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
In a separate statement today, the IMF Executive Board also
said that it has agreed to recommend an increase in member quotas
by 45 percent to the equivalent of approximately 209.5 billion
SDRs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
