<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns US Nuclear Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Iran has condemned the United
States of recent nuclear test while hindering peaceful use of
atomic energy in Iran, Iran's official news agency IRNA said today.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a statement by the Foreign Ministry
spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi Friday night as saying that the
U.S. had been blocking peaceful measures supervised by the
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) while that country had
itself been conducting destructive atomic tests.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the U.S. impediments in peaceful use of
atomic energy was contrary to Washington's commitment to the
Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT).
</P>
<P>
Due to its hostility against the Iranian nation, the spokesman
said, the U.S. has ignored Iran's atomic energy use for peaceful
purposes and adopted a discriminatory attitude vis-a-vis NPT.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the role of IAEA as the sole legal body to
supervise nuclear activities for peaceful purposes, adding that
it was the only agency which could sanction peaceful performance
of countries in using nuclear energy.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that the advanced members of NPT were duty
bound to unconditionally assist other member states for the
peaceful application of atomic energy needed in their development
programs.
</P>
<P>
Iran is now building a 1,000 megawatt nuclear power nuclear
plant near the southern port of Bushehr with help of Russia which
will help Iran complete the project by supplying equipment and
facilities as well as raw materials such as fuel for operation.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent report, Tehran has shown interest in
purchasing nuclear power facilities from India.
</P>
<P>
However, the United States has pressured Russia and other
countries for not having nuclear cooperations with Iran and it is
accusing Tehran of seeking weapons of mass destruction. But
Tehran denied the accusation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970920.0126 </DOCNO>
