<HEADLINE> Mozambique Harvests 230 Investment Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 20 (Xinhua) -- About 230 investment programs
with a total value of 650 million U.S. Dollars have been pooled
into the country during June 1996 and June 1997, local daily
Naticias reported today.
</P>
<P>
Fernando Sumbane, Director of Mozambican Investment Promotion
Center revealed the figures at a Seminar on Private Enterprises
held here this week.
</P>
<P>
Industrial projects have topped the investments with a total
value of about 269 million dollars, followed by agricultural
projects.
</P>
<P>
The Maputo Province ranks as the first in attracting
investment, with its 127 million dollars, the second one being
northern mozambica's Zambezia Province with 90 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Fernando said that with the opening up of the Maputo
Development Corridor and the natural gas field in Inhambane
Province, Mozambique could be expected to receive an investment
of six billion before the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The investment promotion official urged the government to
build duty-free industrial zones and special economic zones.
</P>
