<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sanchez Vicrio Captures Berth in Princess Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of
Spain stormed to her victory over Indonesian Yayuk Basuki 1-6, 7-6
(7-2), 6-4 in a two-and-a-half hours rally, advancing to the
finals of the Toyota Princess Cup tennis tournament on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The unforced errors of Sanchez Vicario helped Basuki race
through the first set with ease, with the latter cherishing the
hope for her first career final.
</P>
<P>
Basuki broke Sanchez Vicario in the first game of the second
set before the second-seeded Spaniard rallied from 0-40 in the
final game to force a tiebreaker which she won 7-2.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario, a former No.1 now ranked 10th, now has won all
five of her matches against Basuki who ranked 22nd.
</P>
<P>
For the second straight year, Sanchez Vicario will face Monica
Seles, a three-time champion after last year's vitory, for the
championship match on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
