<HEADLINE> Mugabe Leaves for U.N. General Assembly Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe left here last night for London enroute to the 52nd
session of the U.N. General Assembly in New York.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe, who is also current Chairman of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU), will deliver a speech on U.N. reform issue.
The 33rd OAU summit, held in harare last june, called
for the reform of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
In the United States, the president is also expected to address
the New York chapter of the U.S. Council on Foreign Relations, and a
breakfast meeting of American Businessmen organized by the U.S.
Corporate Council on Africa.
</P>
<P>
He will also attend an investment drive conference in Miami,
Florida, organized by Africa Resources Limited.
</P>
<P>
The president, who was accompanied by Minister of Foreign Affairs
Stan Mudenge, is expected back home next Sunday. 
</P>
