<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles Advances to Final In Princess Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Monica Seles of the
United States blew past Naoko Sawamatsu of Japan 6-3, 6-1 on
Saturday to advance to the finals of the Toyota Princess Cup
tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Seles' hard and wide shots kept Sawamatsu, who upset third seed
Conchita Martinez of Spain in the quarters, too far off balance
during the 59-minute match in front of 6,000 home spectators.
</P>
<P>
From 3-1 in the second set, the third-ranked American seemed to
step up her pace another notch, letting Sawamatsu win only one
point in the last three games.
</P>
<P>
This will be the seventh final of the year for Seles, who has
won two tournaments, lost three finals to Martina Hingis and once
to Jana Novotna.
</P>
<P>
Seles has won this tournament three times, beating Arantxa
Sanchez Vicario of Spain in the final last year.
</P>
<P>
Seles will meet the winner of the other semifinal between
second seed Sanchez Vicario and fifth seed Indonesia's Yayuk
Basuki. 
</P>
</TEXT>
