<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Shanghai Residents Turn to Real Estate Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 20 (Xinhua) -- A growing number of Shanghai
residents, who are widely known for their adeptness at turning a
profit, have in recent years turned to real estate, a new
investment target which offers high returns and low risks.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey conducted by the Beijing-based Zero
Investigation Co. shows that 1.6 percent of the Shanghai people
are involved in real estate investment.
</P>
<P>
Experts note that the increasingly strong economic strength of
local people is the main factor for the recent recovery of the
real estate market in the largest metropolitan area in China.
</P>
<P>
Local savings deposits at the end of July this year stood at
222.04 billion yuan (26.75 billion US dollars), up 26.2 percent on
the previous year's period. In addition, local urbanites expended
37 percent more for housing in the first six months of this year
than in the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Many residents are currently earning profits by purchasing and
then leasing low-priced housing, with a number of investor buying
apartments in the Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has also introduced a series of
preferential policies to boost the local real estate market, with
local banks providing mortgage loans the purchase of homes.
</P>
<P>
The sluggish market has prompted real estate developers to
adopt innovative methods to promote sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970920.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's 10th National Assembly Opens First Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's newly-elected 10th
National Assembly opened its first session here today with the
participation of 450 deputies selected during the July 20 election.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Communist Party leader Do Muoi, President Le
Duc Anh and Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet attended the opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, Chairman of the Ninth National Assembly
Nong Duc Manh said that the results of the election showed the
people's trust in the party and the government in the cause of
building a country of the people, by the people and for the people.
</P>
<P>
Do Muoi said that the Communist Party of Vietnam would continue
to exercise its leadership through the state law-making, executive
and judicial activities.
</P>
<P>
He urged the government, the national assembly and other state
organs to improve their efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The first session of the Tenth National Assembly is scheduled
to conclude on September 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
