<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Improves Investment Climate for Auto Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Supreme Soviet today
adopted a law to attract more foreign capital and promote domestic
auto industry.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, all joint ventures producing motor vehicles and
spare parts are exempted from taxes in importing necessary
materials before the year of 2008. Besides, those companies are
permitted to import the tax-free goods listed by the Ukrainian
cabinet and their domestic products can be sold without paying
value-added tax.
</P>
<P>
The preconditions are that the investors must fund no less than
150 million U.S. dollars in the fixed assets and those ventures
must employ Ukrainians who account for no less than 90 percent of
the whole staff workers.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian cabinet expressed its satisfaction with the
passing of the law, saying that it will help change the bad
impression of foreigners on the Ukraine's investment environment.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine had issued some preferential policies to foreign-funded
enterprises since 1994. But the parliament cancelled part of those
to increase government revenue at the beginning of the year, which
has resulted in the evacuation of a few large companies of the
United States and Japan from the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
