<HEADLINE> Cuba Qualifies for Volleyball World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 19 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban men spikers
secured their berth to the World Cup by winning its sixth straight
regional championship in Puerto Rico Friday night.
</P>
<P>
With superior work at the net, Cuba defeated the United States
in straight sets 15-11, 15-11, 15-4 to take the title of the North
and Central American and Caribbean championship.
</P>
<P>
The Cubans did not concede a single set in five games in a row,
and the United States failed to pose real challenge in the finals
to the volleyball powerhouse.
</P>
<P>
"We were not really a threat to beat Cuba tonight, and that's
disappointing," lamented U.S. coach Doug Beal.
</P>
<P>
The Americans had their best shot in the second game by clawing
to 11-9 before Ihosvany Hernandez, Cuba's towering outside hitter,
began to take over the game.
</P>
<P>
"We came to qualify for the World Cup, and this is an important
moment for us," said Cuban coach Juan Diaz.
</P>
<P>
Diaz said his team has pinned its hopes on the 2,000 Olympics
as it was about half rookie players.
</P>
<P>
Canada finished third behind the United States after defeating
Mexico 15-9, 15-8, 13-15, 15-9 earlier Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Cuban captain Hernandez was named the tournament Most Valuable
Player. 
</P>
</TEXT>
