<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in India Remarkable: UN Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations' world
investment report for 1997 has rated India's performance in
foreign direct investment inflows as "remarkable," local press
reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. report said that foreign direct investment in India
exceeded portfolio investment inflows for the first time in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
It added that India has become an attractive destination even
for transitional corporations from Asian countries, particularly
from South Korea.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, outflows from South Korea to India are
outstripping those from the United States and the United Kingdom,
traditionally India's largest trade and investment partners.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, foreign direct investment inflows into India surged by
about 34 percent to 2.6 billion U.S. dollars. In 1995, foreign
direct investment increased by 47 percent to 1.9 billion dollars
from the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
