<HEADLINE> Vientiane Residents' Per Capita Income Surges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 19 (Xinhua) -- The per capita income of the
residents in the Lao capital of Vientiane will rise to 750
U.S. dollars in the 1997-1998 period, the official news agency KPL
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The city projected a 10-11 percent growth of gross domestic
product (GDP) for the period. Agro-forestry is expected to grow
six percent, industry and handicraft five percent and service
industry 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
It reported a 12 percent economic growth in the 1996-97
period. Agro-forestry rose 12 percent, industry and handicraft 10
percent and services and tourism 17 percent.
</P>
<P>
Inflation rate for 1996-1997 was 7.3 percent and per-capita
income reached 715 dollars, the agency said. 
</P>
