<HEADLINE> Italy Ties Sweden 1-1 in Davis Cup Semifinal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Sweden and Italy split the
first two singles matches for a 1-1 tie in their Davis Cup World
Group semifinal in Norrkoping, Sweden on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Renzo Furlan defeated Thomas Enqvist to keep alive the hopes of
Italy against favourite Sweden with a win apiece on the first day
of their best-of-five semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Furlan, ranked 84th in the world, scored a full-set victory of
3-6, 6-3, 6-4, 3-6, 6-3 against Enqvist, who slipped to 15th in
the world rankings after a series of injuries and illnesses.
</P>
<P>
Jonas Bjorkman, the highest-ranked Swede at 13th in the world,
won the opener in another full-set conflict by beating Omar
Camporese 6-7 (5-7), 6-3, 6-2, 3-6, 6-3 for a morale-boosing one
point for the host.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman and Nicklas Kulti, doubles finalists at the U.S.
Open, will meet Camporese and Diego Nargiso in Saturday's
doubles. 
</P>
