<HEADLINE> Japan Draws UAE Goalless in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 19 (Xinhua) -- With a goal ruled offside,
Japan had to settle for a scoreless draw against home squad the
United Arab Emirates here on Friday in the second-round Asian
World Cup qualifier.
</P>
<P>
Masami Ihara swung in his clean header in the 75th minute but
teammate Norio Omura was caught offside by linesman Miniandi
Alagokofen ahead of the play.
</P>
<P>
The shocked home fans were saved from the brink of breaking
tears as Malaysian referee Mohammed Abdullah nullified the goal to
their relief.
</P>
<P>
The draw left both Japan and the Emirates with 1-1-0 records
and four points, two behind Group B leader South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Due to heat and humidity, Japan started the match cautiously,
leaving all the initiatives to the home team in the first 15
minutes. But the temperatues also affected the home squad and
Japan managed to take control of the game.
</P>
<P>
Emirates keeper Mohsin Mussabeh denied the Japanese several
chances while Japanese striker Kazuyochi Miura was closely marked
throughout the game.
</P>
<P>
The Emirates will meet Japan again in Tokyo on October 26.
</P>
<P>
Only the group winner qualifies automatically for France. The
runner-up enters a playoff with the Group A runner-up for a third
berth. The playoff loser than faces Australia for another place
in the 32-nation finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
