<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Brazil Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Brazil got 10.2
billion U.S. dollars in direct foreign investments during the
first eight months of this year, the Central Bank announced today.
</P>
<P>
August's foreign direct capitals amounted to 1.42 billion
dollars. Among them, 881 million dollars, or 62 percent, went to
privatizations, said the Bank.
</P>
<P>
Up to September 16, foreign investments reached 1.04 billion
dollars, and 715 million dollars of it, or 68 percent, were used
to buy an electronics firm.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is expected to receive 15 billion dollars in direct
foreign investments this year, it said. 
</P>
