western port city of Walvis Bay.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Friday said the items, from one of the
two military planes believed to have collided off the Namibian
coast last Saturday, were brought to Walvis Bay by a fishing
vessel which traveled 33 hours from the scene.
</P>
<P>
It is not yet known if the burnt pieces belong to the German
military plane or the American air force transport aircraft, which
crashed over the south Atlantic. (Namibia-German Plane)
