<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan Press Hails Free Trade Pact With Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, September 19 (Xinhua) -- A Nicaraguan newspaper today
hailed the signing of a free trade pact with Mexico as a first
step to enter the world economy.
</P>
<P>
Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo and his Nicaraguan
counterpart Arnoldo Aleman announced Thursday night that they have
finished the negotiations and signed a bilateral free trade
agreement.
</P>
<P>
The "La Tribuna" daily said that this agreement could lead
Nicaragua into the world economy. "But it is too soon to sing
victory," it cautioned.
</P>
<P>
The road has been bumpy since 1991 when the Violeta Chamorro
government started the process, the paper said. "Mexican tariff
barriers to Nicaraguan goods caused the suspension of negotiations
in 1994." 
</P>
</TEXT>
