<HEADLINE> Kuwait Defeats Qatar 2-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait won its away game
2-0 against Qatar in Doha on Friday in the second-round Asian
World Cup qualifier.
</P>
<P>
Jassim al-Huwaidy blasted into the net with his right-footed
kick in the 18th minute before Bashar Abdullah added the second in
the 89th minute in a perfect counter attack.
</P>
<P>
The win raised the morale for the Kuwaiti as they lost the
opener 2-1 to Saudi Arabia on Sunday for a 1-0-1 slate in Group A
with three points, one behind group leaders Iran and Saudi Arabia
which drew 1-1 earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
A flurry of attacks kept Qatar's goalie Yunis Ahmad busy in
saves one after another, making Qatar looked disorganized for most
of the game.
</P>
<P>
Qatar's first real chance came in the dying minutes of the
first half when Nasser Kamil's shot was saved by Kuwait's
goalkeeper Khaled al-Fadli.
</P>
<P>
The group winner qualifies automatically for France with the
runner-up entering a playoff with the second-placed team from
Group B.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the playoff qualifies while the loser still can
reach the 32-nation finals if it wins a two-leg series with
Oceania winner Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
