<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Players Enter Six Finals in World Acrobatics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, September 19 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese players
displayed inspiring fighting power, entering six finals of the
seven events at the on-going 1997 World Sports Acrobatics
Championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the second round of the men's pair competition, Chinese
world champions Song Min and Li Renjie, who are tipped to win all
three titles of the event, consolidated their dominating position
by running away with a total of 19.96 points.
</P>
<P>
However, in the women's pair's tempo clashes, China's new
combination Liao Xinxin adn Lao Peiling, who topped the event's
ranking in the first round, almost lost their leading spot to
Ukrainian arch-rivals by scoring only 9.80 points.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese duo was expected to fight fierce battles in order
to win the top honor in the event.
</P>
<P>
The men's tumbling event was the Chinese squad's Achilles
tendon, with no hope of winning any of its three titles. However,
Chen Bo and Zhao Gang beat the tide to squeeze into the final,
giving a morale boost to their compatriots.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Chinese players in the mixed pair, women's and
men's groups events have maintained their favorable positions to
book their berths in the finals.
</P>
<P>
About 14 of the 21 titles of the World Sports Acrobatics
Championships would be unveiled Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinse delegation, which pocketed eight titles in 1996, is
likely to fight a uphill battle over the next two days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
