<HEADLINE> United States Moves Closer to Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras and Michael
Chang won their opening matches to give the United States a 2-0
lead in the semifinals of the 59th Davis Cup on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Michael Chang avenged one of the most difficult losses of his
career by beating U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter 6-4, 1-6, 6-3,
6-4 in a classic battle of a baseline vesus serve-and-volley.
</P>
<P>
The second match featured two of the biggest servers in the
sport. And Pete Sampras proved that he was the world number one by
routing Australian Mark Philippoussis 6-1, 6-2, 7-6 (7/5).
</P>
<P>
The United States is expected to clinch the victory in the
best-of-five contest but Australia may keep its hopes alive on
Saturday when the doubles will feature its world's top-rated
doubles player of Mark Woodforde and Todd Woodbridge against
American Todd Martin and Jim Courier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
