<HEADLINE> S. Korea Takes Asian Men's Basketball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, September 19 (Xinhua) -- South Korea outscored its
Japanese rivals 78-76 in a close final to take the 19th Asian
Men's Basketball Championship in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia on Friday.
</P>
<P>
From a 40-43 deficit at half break, South Korea who upset China
in the cross match Thursday, spared no efforts in each turn of the
ball and clawed back to beat the Japanese by a slim margin of two
points.
</P>
<P>
This was the first gold medal for the South Koreans in the
Asian Men's Basketball history.
</P>
<P>
In the third-place play-off, China beat host Saudi Arabia 96-68
to take home a disappointing bronze medal. 
</P>
