<HEADLINE> U.S. B-1 Bomber Crashes, Four Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 19 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Air Force B-1
strategic bomber crashed Friday over the northwestern U.S. state
of Montana, killing all four crew members on board of it, a
Pentagon official said.
</P>
<P>
The crash, the sixth in a string of accidents involving
U.S. military planes in a week, occurred at about 2210 GMT at the
Powder River military range during a training mission, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
The cause or circumstances of the crash was not immediately
known.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Defense Secretary William Cohen have ordered a 24-hour
grounding of aircraft for checking. 
</P>
