<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina's Steel Output Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's steel output
registered increases in August compared with the same period of
1996 in three of the four stages of steel production, according to
the Steel Industrialists Center.
</P>
<P>
The output of cold rolled products grew 18.7 percent to 122,00
tons, while that of hot rolled products rose 9.1 percent to
396,800 tons.
</P>
<P>
The raw steel production of 357,800 tons represented a 1.6
percent growth.
</P>
<P>
Pig iron production totaled 256,600 tons, down 11.6 percent
from that of the corresponding previous period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
