<HEADLINE> Beijing Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
All newspapers carry banner headlines in red letters and photos
in their front pages about the First Plenum of the 15th Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) which elected on
Friday the members and alternate members of the Political Bureau
of the CPC Central Committee, members of the Standing Committee of
the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and the General
Secretary of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The new Political Bureau Standing Committee is composed of
Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei
Jianxing and Li Lanqing. Jiang is the General Secretary of the CPC
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
All also carry profiles of the newly-elected Party leaders.
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The paper publishes the full text of the communique of the
First Plenum of the 15th CPC Central Committee. The Plenum was
attended by 191 full members and 151 alternate members of the CPC
Central Committee. Jiang Zemin presided over the plenum and
delivered an important speech.
</P>
<P>
-- The re-elected General Secretary of the CPC Central
Committee Jiang Zemin met yesterday with delegates from the army
and the armed police to the 15th CPC National Congress. Jiang
called on them to advance along the road of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics pioneered by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
-- The paper runs an editorial, entitled "Strong Core of
Leadership to Lead China to 21st Century", to hail the formation
of the new central leadership, which says that the election
accords with the aspiration of the people across China and of the
whole Party.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraphy"
</P>
<P>
-- People throughout China celebrated the successful conclusion
of the 15th CPC National Congress and the formation of the new
Party leadership with Jiang Zemin as its core. They voiced their
pledge to study the carry out decisions made at the congress,
rally closely round the new Party leadership, and hold high the
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
-- The Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the
CPC, elected by the 15th CPC National Congress, held its first
plenary session yesterday.
</P>
<P>
-- Two books on Deng Xiaoping Theory have been published to
help promote the study of the theory.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Party General Secretary Jiang Zemin along with six other
members of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the
CPC Central Committee met Friday with Chinese and foreign
reporters shortly after te conclusion of the First Plenum of the
15th CPC Central Committee. Jiang introduced the newly-elected CPC
leaders to the press at the Great Hall of the People. 
</P>
