<HEADLINE> Iran Draws Saudi Arabia 1-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Iran put up a spirited fight
against Saudi Arabia at Tehran's Azadi stadium but had to settle
for a 1-1 draw due to brave saves by the Saudi goalie on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was the second match for Iran in group A at the Asian zone
final qualifying round for the 1998 World Cup finals. Early on
September 13, Iran rallied from two-goal deficit to beat China 4-2
in its away game.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi squad scored the first goal with 35 minutes into the
game before the Iranians equalized in the 65th minute.
</P>
<P>
The Iran-Saudi Arabia encounter was a blessing for all Iranians
as they were given a day off.
</P>
<P>
The host squad displayed its might by shotting at least three
times against the Saudis whose goalie made perfect dives to thwart
at least four dangerous shots.
</P>
<P>
As the game ended in a draw, both Iran and Saudi Arabia kept
their winning streak intact as each scored victories in their
respective openers in the group. 
