<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Pacific Forum Appoints New Secretary General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RAROTONGA, Cook Islands, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Leaders
attending the 28th South Pacific Forum meeting have agreed to
appoint Noel Levi of Papua New Guinea as the Secretary General for
the next three years starting January 1998.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached yesterday by the leaders at their
retreat at Aitutaki, about 250 km north of here, said a forum
media statement released here today.
</P>
<P>
The term of the current Secretary General Ieremia T. Tabai
comes to an end next January after serving six years in office.
</P>
<P>
Levi was an experienced diplomat, working as PNG's foreign
minister, ambassador to China and high commissioner to Britain
and North Ireland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
